findings.title: Safe math
findings.description: Using solidity version lower than 0.8.0 can cause code blocks without safe math to fail if inappropriate values are used.

findings.title: Solidity Version Acceptable
findings.description: The solidity version acceptable for the contract is ">=0.6.0 <0.9.0". If the Solidity version would be lower than 0.8.0, then code blocks without safe math could fail.

findings.title: swapBack function distributes reflection and marketing fee and adds liquidity
findings.description: The swapBack function is responsible for distributing reflection and marketing fees as well as adding liquidity.

findings.title: Liquidity Fee Part Goes to Reflection
findings.description: If dynamic liquidity fee will equal to zero, liquidity fee part goes to reflection.

findings.title: Unaudited Reflector(Cashier) Interface
findings.description: The reflector(Cashier) interface is provided but its actual working and functions are not audited.
